Description: This plugin reports the sitemap of the web application.

Proof: <script>alert(1)</script> was reflected in the response body.
Plugin Output: The parameter searchQuery is vulnerable to cross-site scripting.
Description: A cross-site scripting vulnerability exists in the searchQuery parameter of the /search endpoint. An attacker could inject malicious scripts.
Steps to Remediate: Sanitize all user input and encode output. Use Content-Security-Policy headers.

Proof: No anti-CSRF token was found in the form submission.
Plugin Output: The form at /account/update does not include a CSRF token.
Description: A cross-site request forgery vulnerability was detected in the account update form. The form does not include an anti-CSRF token.
Steps to Remediate: Implement anti-CSRF tokens in all state-changing forms. Use the SameSite cookie attribute.

Proof: Server: Apache/2.4.49 was disclosed in the HTTP response headers.
Plugin Output: The server banner reveals version information.
Description: The web server discloses its version in HTTP response headers, which may aid attackers in identifying known vulnerabilities.
Steps to Remediate: Configure the web server to suppress version information in response headers.
